 To Be Nsala’s Daughter traces the past and present of the colonial gaze both in Congo and in the author’s lived experience as a mixed-race Black woman in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAtrocitieszCongo (Democratic Republic). 0aDocumentary photographyzCongo (Democratic Republic). 0aViolencezCongo (Democratic Republic). 7aPhotography / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023722?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023722423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023722/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles